Type: Package
Package: fontgis
Title: A simple way to use GIS icons in R for spatial visualisation and analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("antony", "barja", , "geografope@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Insert 'Font-GIS' icon sets into 'R Markdown' documents, 'Quarto' files, and 'Shiny' applications in a simple and flexible way.
             The icons, designed for GIS and spatial analysis themes, can be integrated as 'SVG' elements or HTML '<i>' tags.
             They can also be exported as 'PNG' images for use in contexts requiring raster graphics.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports: 
    htmltools,
    lifecycle,
    rlang,
    tidyr,
    webshot2,
    glue
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
URL: http://geografo.pe/fontgis/
